My review is going to be long........ First and foremost i am a daughter of a reverend minister in a pentecostal church, i could relate so well with alot of scenes from this movie, most Pastors and Reverend abandon their family especially their kids when they are called to ministry, they just automatically think that God will raise their kids without their efforts, they disciple other people's children, teach, preach and counsel other people except their own .....and the "mummy G Os" almost nevr get a say, cos they have to be with their husband anywhre he goes to do ministry. I am saying this out of experience! That i am still a Christian serving God and doing God's work now . ......i found God as an adult NOT bcos my father was a reverend minister. Alot of us pastor's kids go astray alot just bcos the shepherd abandoned the sheep/s .......we preach about God's love but barely show it! We barely enjoyed the love of our father ,family time has been scarified for "Holy Ghost hour" and revivals ........(Don't get me wrong, those are powerful programs, too) Another point is, whoever said your child must be a pastor to take over from you , most of our Christian parents, leaders, elders etc they despise the young ones and their giftings thinking it is from the devil, how about you supporting that gift and helping those youth , cos when you don't guide and help them become the best, guess what??? The devil's offer is juicy, and they will leave the church and switch .........i have seen this happen to a lot of musicians in my choir days. How about the body of Christ build and create their own record labels for the Singers and called musicials to thrive also ........it can be hard being a gospel music artist with no support, not even from their place of worship where they've served for years without collecting anything, for a long time the Church has thrown away alot of talents...........mehn there is just alot to be said about these things but let me drop my pen here ...... i thank God for this movie ........ thank God for the pastors , fathers, and leaders who are doing it right .
